# Bene — Decentralized Fundraising Platform (Ergo)

![Bene Logo](static/favicon.png)

## Overview

**Bene** is a fully decentralized, client-side fundraising platform built on the **Ergo blockchain**, implementing a **Proof-of-Funding** model.  
It removes the need for trust in centralized intermediaries by enforcing fundraising logic entirely through immutable smart contracts.

Projects can access funds **only if predefined success conditions are met**, while contributors are guaranteed refunds in case of failure.

---

## Key Properties

- **Trustless Fundraising:** Funds are governed exclusively by smart contracts.
- **Client-Side Only:** No backend servers, databases, or custodial services.
- **Censorship Resistant:** Users connect directly to Ergo nodes and explorers.
- **Deterministic Rules:** Contract logic defines all outcomes — no discretion.

---

## Architecture Overview

### Serverless & Sovereign by Design

Bene follows a **100% client-side architecture**:

- No centralized backend or API servers
- No proprietary databases
- Direct blockchain interaction from the browser
- User-controlled choice of Ergo nodes and explorers

All business logic, custody, and validation are handled on-chain.

