## User Guide (Contributors)

### Token Model

Bene uses a dual-token mechanism to ensure transparent accounting.

#### 1. Auxiliary Project Token (APT)

- Acts as a **temporary receipt** for user contributions
- Represents the contributor’s claim within a campaign
- Used to either:
  - Redeem **PFTs** on success
  - Claim a **full refund** on failure

#### 2. Proof-Funding Token (PFT)

- The **actual project token**
- Released only if the campaign succeeds
- Distributed proportionally to contributors who exchange APTs

---

### Contribution Lifecycle

#### 1. Contribution Phase
- Users contribute ERG or a specified base token
- Funds are locked in the contract
- APTs are minted and issued to contributors
- PFTs remain locked until campaign resolution

#### 2. Resolution Phase

| Outcome | Condition | User Action |
|------|---------|------------|
| Success | Tokens Sold ≥ Minimum Goal (R5) | Exchange APT → PFT |
| Failure | Deadline passed (R4) and goal unmet | Return APT → Full Refund |

---

### On-Chain Discussions

- Campaigns include a **fully on-chain comment system**
- Discussions are immutable and censorship-resistant
- Based on the Reputation Systems Forum Protocol  
  https://github.com/reputation-systems/forum-application

---

## Guide for Project Creators

### Requirements

- Pre-minted **Project Tokens (PFT)**
- APT is generated automatically by the platform

### Fees

- **5% developer fee**
- Applied **only if the campaign succeeds**
- No fees charged on failed campaigns

---

### Campaign Parameters (Immutable)

- **R4 — Deadline**
- **R5 — Minimum Goal**
- **R7 — Token Price**
- **R8 — Configuration (Owner, Fee Address, Token IDs)**

---

### Fund Management Rules

| Action | Condition |
|------|----------|
| Withdraw Funds | Campaign success |
| Withdraw Unsold PFTs | Anytime (security invariant enforced) |
| Add PFT Stock | Anytime |

